Logging Infrastructure

Purpose: Logging abstraction and concrete implementations for structured application logging.

What belongs here:
- Logger interface or abstract base class (ILogger / TBaseLogger)
- File logger implementation with log rotation support
- Console/terminal logger implementation
- Structured JSON logger for log aggregation systems
- Log level definitions (Debug, Info, Warning, Error, Fatal)
- Log entry DTO with timestamp, level, source, message, and context data
- Log formatting utilities (plain text, JSON, key=value)
- Thread-safe logger factory or singleton access

Design rules:
- All loggers must be thread-safe for concurrent WebBroker request handling.
- Never log passwords, tokens, authorization headers, or sensitive payloads.
- Log level must be configurable at runtime.
- Prefer injecting ILogger into services rather than calling a global singleton directly.

